The diagnostic test identifies what your child already knows and what they still need to learn. The results help teachers plan the best learning methods to enhance their learning. MDE has revamped and relaunched its ‚ÄúStrong Readers‚Äù website to help families assist their children with building their reading skills. The site is organized by grade level, from Kindergarten through grade 5 and includes strategies for developing stronger reader habits and a series of activities to practice the five components of reading (sound, phonics, fluency, vocabulary and comprehension). Tools are also included to assist families with locating books to match their child‚Äôs grade band and a free online library.

Web Link: https://strongreadersms.com/

post_text:
NPSD Coronavirus (COVID-19) Update

The North Panola school District will be closed for students through April 17, 2020.

During this time, Governor Reeves has ensured that schools will continue to receive funding and all employees will be paid during the closure according to House Bill 1647 (HB 1647) which states that all public school districts ‚Äúmay‚Äù grant administrative leave with pay to all employees during this time period; placing the authority in the hands of the local school districts to determine ground rules for payment or none payment of employees during this time.

Small groups of staff members will be requested to come in for work on a rotational schedule to help maintain the practice of social distancing.

The District will continue to supply meals to students throughout this time.

Learning will continue throughout the school closure period via learning packets (paper/pencil) and online enrichment activities. Packets will be available for students on Wednesday, March 25th from 10 am to 6 pm at all school sites for parents to pickup.

Small groups of staff members will be requested to come in for work on a rotational schedule to help maintain the practice of social distancing.

The District will continue to supply meals to students throughout this time.

post_text: SkillsUSA members are selling handcrafted, customized Cougar Paw Door Hangers. These wooden door hangers can be used inside or outside of your home, office, or dorm room. Each Paw Print is customized to your specifications. Painted Paws are $20 and Unfinished Paws are $10 Complete the form by following the link ( http://forms.gle/x48iGmEcTZ22bz2U7 ) or use your cell phone to scan the QR code to place your order. You can also stop by the North Panola Career & Technical Center at 601 Railroad Street in Como, MS. All proceeds will help finished their SkillsUSA State Competition in Jackson, MS.

This week, February 3-7, is National School Counseling Week. The theme is "School Counselors: Helping Build Better Humans", and we will be showing appreciation for the many things that our district's counseling program provides to our NPSD students and the impact they can have in helping students achieve school success and plan for a career.
#NSCW

This week, February 3-7, is National School Counseling Week. #NSCW

post_text:
Happy National School Counseling Week to NPSD Counselors!

Superintendent Richardson signed a proclamation declaring February 3-7, 2020 as National School Counseling Week in North Panola School District. NSCW highlights the tremendous impact school counselors can have in helping students achieve school success and plan for a career.

This special week honoring school counselors provides recognition for school counselors who implement comprehensive school counseling programs, a vital part of the educational process for all students as they meet the challenges of the 21st century.
